The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 The Indian Railways and the State Bank of India have jointly launched a co-branded credit card and a loyalty programme, called Subh Yatra. The cardholders of SBI Railways Card will get loyalty points every time they log on to the Indian Railway Catering and Tourism Corporation website to buy railway tickets. The membership fee for this card is Rs 500 for the first year. 

 JM Mutual Fund has launched an open-ended equity scheme, called JM Hi-fi Fund. The new fund offer closes on March 20 and the minimum investment is Rs 5,000. There is no entry load, but investments below Rs 3 crore will attract a penalty of 2.25 per cent if exited within six months.

 Franklin Templeton Mutual Fund has announced dividends and bonus under five of its schemes, namely, the India Income Builder, Monthly Income Plan, Government Securities Fund and Short Term Income Plan. 

 Bank of Maharashtra has launched two offerings under its current account scheme to attract more high-value customers. These plans are called Mahabank-Pearl and Mahabank-Sapphire These schemes offer concessions up to 60 per cent across various service charges.




